48. **Scene:** Elara holds the ashes, and a single page floats up—*“I’m still here.”*  

49. **Protagonist:** A street vendor named Tariq, who sells clocks that stop time for one person;  
50. **Dilemma:** He must decide whether to sell a clock to a man who wants to stop time to save his dying wife—or keep it, knowing it will cost him his own time;  
51. **Decision:** He sells it, but the clock stops *him* instead;  
52. **Climax:** Tariq watches the man’s wife die—while he stands frozen in time, unable to move;  
53. **Outcome:** The man returns the clock, but it’s now a blank face—*“I didn’t need to stop time. I just needed to be there.”*  
54. **Clever Twist:** The clocks don’t stop time—they *steal* it from the seller;  
55. **Clever Worldbuilding Feature:** In this city, time is currency—every second is a coin, and the clocks are the only way to trade it;  
56. **Scene:** Tariq’s hands are frozen mid-reach—*“I just wanted to help.”*  

